sufficienttofund2,198scholarshipsinFY27. Ifthefull$1,705,000infirstyearcostsanticipated
by the Department are deducted, the remaining $8,782,600 would be sufficient to fund 1,841
scholarships, with more scholarships funded in future years as the one-time system change cost
is not deducted. It is assumed for the purposes of this fiscal note that revenues in future years
willgrowbysomeindeterminableamount.

